name: Overheat
description: Lowers the user's Special Attack by 2 stages after use.

name: Pain Split
description: Calculates the average of the user's current HP and the target's HP; the HP of both Pokemon is set to this average. Pokemon can be healed by Pain Split even under the effects of Heal Block.

name: Pay Day
description: The player picks up extra money after in-game battles; the money received is equal to: [user's level * 5 * number of times Pay Day is used]. The player does not lose money if the opponent uses Pay Day but the player wins the battle.

name: Peck
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Perish Song
description: All active Pokemon will faint in 3 turns unless they are switched out.

name: Petal Dance
description: The user attacks uncontrollably for 2-3 turns and then gets confused.

name: Pin Missile
description: Attacks 2-5 times in one turn; if one of these attacks breaks a target's Substitute the target will take damage for the rest of the hits. This move has a 3/8 chance to hit twice a 3/8 chance to hit three times a 1/8 chance to hit four times and a 1/8 chance to hit five times. If the user of this move has Skill Link this move will always strike five times.

name: Poison Fang
description: Has a 30% chance to inflict Toxic poison on the target.

name: Poison Gas
description: Poisons the target.

name: Poison Sting
description: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.

name: Poison Tail
description: Has a high critical hit ratio and a 10% chance to poison the target.

name: PoisonPowder
description: Poisons the target.

name: Pound
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Powder Snow
description: Has a 10% chance to freeze the target.

name: Present
description: Randomly either attacks with a variable power between 40 base power and 120 base power or heals the target by 80 HP.

name: Protect
description: Almost always goes first. The user is protected from all attacks for one turn but the move's success rate halves with each consecutive use of Protect Detect or Endure. If a Pokemon has No Guard or used Lock-On or Mind Reader against the user during the previous turn its attack has a [100 Varmove's normal accuracy]% chance to hit through Protect; OHKO moves do not benefit from this effect. Blizzard has a 30% to hit through this move during Hail as does Thunder during Rain Dance.

name: Psybeam
description: Has a 10% chance to confuse the target.

name: Psych Up
description: The user copies all six of the target's current stat modifiers.

name: Psychic
description: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.

name: Psycho Boost
description: Lowers the user's Special Attack by 2 stages after use.

name: Psywave
description: Randomly inflicts set damage equal to .5x .6x .7x .8x .9x 1.0x 1.1x 1.2x 1.3x 1.4x or 1.5x the user's level.

name: Pursuit
description: If the target switches out on the current turn this move strikes with doubled power before the switch. Baton Passers still escape safely. When a faster Pokemon uses Pursuit against a U-Turner the U-Turner is hit for normal damage; when a slower Pokemon uses Pursuit against a U-Turner the U-Turner makes its attack then is hit by Pursuit for double power and switches out.

name: Quick Attack
description: Usually goes first.

name: Rage
description: The user's Attack rises by 1 stage if attacked before its next move.

name: Rain Dance
description: Cancels all other weather moves. For 5 turns: the power of Water attacks is increased by 50% the power of Fire attacks is decreased by 50% Thunder never misses and has a 30% chance to hit through Protect and Detect the power of Solarbeam is halved and the healing power of Morning Sun Synthesis and Moonlight is decreased from 1/2 to 1/4 of the user's max HP. The effects of Rain Dance will last for eight turns if its user is holding Damp Rock.

name: Rapid Spin
description: Removes Spikes Stealth Rock Toxic Spikes and Leech Seed from the user's side of the field; also frees the user from Bind Clamp Fire Spin Magma Storm Sand Tomb Whirlpool and Wrap. These effects do not occur if the move misses or is used against Ghost-type Pokemon.

name: Razor Leaf
description: Has a high critical hit ratio.

name: Razor Wind
description: The user prepares on turn one becoming uncontrollable and then attacks on turn two. Has a high critical hit ratio.

name: Recover
description: Restores 1/2 of the user's max HP.

name: Recycle
description: The user's lost item is recovered. Items lost to Bug Bite Fling Natural Gift and Pluck will be recovered if the user of Recycle was the item's original holder; items lost to Trick Switcheroo Thief Covet or Knock Off cannot be recovered.

name: Reflect
description: All Pokemon in the user's party receive 1/2 damage from Physical attacks for 5 turns. Reflect will be removed from the user's field if an opponent's Pokemon uses Brick Break. It will also last for eight turns if its user is holding Light Clay. In double battles both Pokemon are shielded but damage protection is reduced from 1/2 to 1/3.

name: Refresh
description: The user recovers from burn poison and paralysis.

name: Rest
description: The user is cured of status effects (and confusion) and recovers full HP but falls asleep for 2 turns. Pokemon who have Early Bird will wake up one turn early.

name: Return
description: Power increases as user's happiness increases; maximum 102 BP.

name: Revenge
description: Almost always goes last even after another Pokemon's Focus Punch; this move's base power doubles if the user is damaged before its turn.

name: Reversal
description: Base power increases as the user's HP decreases.

name: Roar
description: Almost always goes last; in trainer battles the target is switched out for a random member of its team. Escapes from wild battles. Has no effect if the target has Suction Cups Soundproof or used Ingrain.

name: Rock Blast
description: Attacks 2-5 times in one turn; if one of these attacks breaks a target's Substitute the target will take damage for the rest of the hits. This move has a 3/8 chance to hit twice a 3/8 chance to hit three times a 1/8 chance to hit four times and a 1/8 chance to hit five times. If the user of this move has Skill Link this move will always strike five times.

name: Rock Slide
description: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.

name: Rock Smash
description: Has a 50% chance to lower the target's Defense by 1 stage.

name: Rock Throw
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Rock Tomb
description: Lowers the target's Speed by 1 stage.

name: Role Play
description: The user's own ability is overwritten with the target's ability; does nothing if the target's ability is Wonder Guard.

name: Rolling Kick
description: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.

name: Rollout
description: The user attacks uncontrollably for five turns; this move's power doubles after each turn and also if Defense Curl was used beforehand. Its power resets after five turns have ended or if the attack misses.

name: Sacred Fire
description: Has a 50% chance to burn the target; can be used while frozen which both attacks the target normally and thaws the user.

name: Safeguard
description: Protects the user's entire team from status conditions for five turns.

name: Sand Tomb
description: Traps the target for 5-6 turns causing damage equal to 1/16 of its max HP each turn; this trapped effect can be broken by Rapid Spin. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-Turn.

name: Sand-Attack
description: Lowers the target's Accuracy by 1 stage.

name: Sandstorm
description: Cancels all other weather moves. For 5 turns: the Special Defense of Rock-type Pokemon is boosted by 50% each active Pokemon even when protected by a Substitute loses 1/16 of its max HP unless it has Sand Veil or is a Ground- Rock- or Steel-type the power of Solarbeam is halved and the healing power of Morning Sun Synthesis and Moonlight is halved. The effects of Sandstorm will last for eight turns if its user is holding Smooth Rock.

name: Scary Face
description: Lowers the target's Speed by 2 stages.

name: Scratch
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Screech
description: Lowers the target's Defense by 2 stages.

name: Secret Power
description: This move has a 30% chance to inflict a side effect depending on the battle's current terrain. The target may be put to sleep in any type of grass (or in puddles) its Attack may be lowered by 1 stage while surfing on any body of water its Speed may be lowered by 1 stage while on marshy terrain its Accuracy may be lowered by 1 stage on beach sand desert sand and dirt paths (and also in Wifi battles) it may flinch in caves or on rocky outdoor terrain it may become frozen on snowy terrain and it may become paralyzed everywhere else.

name: Seismic Toss
description: Does damage equal to user's level.

name: Selfdestruct
description: Causes the user to faint.

name: Shadow Ball
description: Has a 20% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.

name: Shadow Punch
description: Ignores Evasion and Accuracy modifiers and never misses except against Protect Detect or a target in the middle of Dig Fly Dive or Bounce.

name: Sharpen
description: Raises the user's Attack by 1 stage.

name: Sheer Cold
description: The target faints; doesn't work on higher-leveled Pokemon.

name: Shock Wave
description: Ignores Evasion and Accuracy modifiers and never misses except against Protect Detect or a target in the middle of Dig Fly Dive or Bounce.

name: Signal Beam
description: Has a 10% chance to confuse the target.

name: Silver Wind
description: Has a 10% chance to raise all of the user's stats by 1 stage.

name: Sing
description: Puts the target to sleep.

name: Sketch
description: The user permanently replaces Sketch with the last move used by the target. Sketch cannot copy itself Chatter Memento or Struggle. Transform and moves that generate other moves can be Sketched successfully as can Explosion and Selfdestruct if a Pokemon with Damp is present. Healing Wish and Lunar Dance can be Sketched because they automatically fail when the user is the last Pokemon of its team. This move fails automatically when selected in wireless or Wi-Fi battles.

name: Skill Swap
description: The user exchanges abilities with the target; does not work if Wonder Guard is the ability of either the user or the target.

name: Skull Bash
description: The user prepares on turn one raising its Defense by 1 stage and becoming uncontrollable and then attacks on turn two.

name: Sky Attack
description: The user prepares on turn one becoming uncontrollable and then attacks on turn two. Also has a 30% chance to make the target flinch.

name: Sky Uppercut
description: Also hits targets in mid-air via Fly or Bounce.

name: Slack Off
description: Restores 1/2 of the user's max HP.

name: Slam
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Slash
description: Has a high critical hit ratio.

name: Sleep Powder
description: Puts the target to sleep.

name: Sleep Talk
description: Does nothing if the user is awake. If the user asleep it randomly performs one of its attacks. Rest will fail if it is selected. Sleep Talk's generated attacks do not cost PP but it cannot generate moves with 0 PP itself Assist Bide Chatter Copycat Disabled attacks Focus Punch Me First Metronome Mirror Move Uproar or attacks with a charge-up turn like Fly or Skull Bash. (Moves with a recharge turn like Hyper Beam can be generated.)

name: Sludge
description: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.

name: Sludge Bomb
description: Has a 30% chance to poison the target.

name: SmellingSalt
description: If the target is paralyzed power is doubled but the target will be cured.

name: Smog
description: Has a 40% chance to poison the target.

name: SmokeScreen
description: Lowers the target's Accuracy by 1 stage.

name: Snatch
description: Almost always goes first. Until the end of the turn the user will steal a supporting move from another Pokemon (including teammates). In double battles Snatch only steals the first applicable move performed by another Pokemon before wearing off.

name: Snore
description: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch; fails if user is awake.

name: Softboiled
description: Restores 1/2 of the user's max HP.

name: SolarBeam
description: The user prepares on turn one becoming uncontrollable and then attacks on turn two. During Sunny Day this move fires immediately; during Rain Dance Sandstorm and Hail this move has half power.

name: SonicBoom
description: Always deals 20 points of damage.

name: Spark
description: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target.

name: Spider Web
description: As long as the user remains in battle the target cannot switch out unless it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-Turn. The target will still be trapped if the user switches out by using Baton Pass.

name: Spike Cannon
description: Attacks 2-5 times in one turn; if one of these attacks breaks a target's Substitute the target will take damage for the rest of the hits. This move has a 3/8 chance to hit twice a 3/8 chance to hit three times a 1/8 chance to hit four times and a 1/8 chance to hit five times. If the user of this move has Skill Link this move will always strike five times.

name: Spikes
description: Damages opponents unless they are Flying-type or have Levitate every time they are switched in; hits through Wonder Guard. Can be used up to three times: saps 1/8 of max HP with one layer 3/16 of max HP with two layers and 1/4 of max HP for three layers.

name: Spit Up
description: Power increases with user's Stockpile count; fails with zero Stockpiles.

name: Spite
description: The target's most recent move is reduced by 4 PP; this fails if the target has not yet performed a move if the target's last move has run out of PP or if the target can only use Struggle.

name: Splash
description: Doesn't do anything (but we still love it). Unfortunately it also cannot be used during the effects of Gravity! :(

name: Spore
description: Puts the target to sleep.

name: Steel Wing
description: Has a 10% chance to raise the user's Defense by 1 stage.

name: Stockpile
description: Can be used up to three times to power Spit Up or Swallow. Also raises the user's Defense and Special Defense by 1 stage each. Stockpiles and the defensive boosts are lost when these Swallow or Spit Up is used or the user switches out. However the boosts can be Baton Passed.

name: Stomp
description: Has a 30% chance to make the target flinch; also retains its normal accuracy and gains doubled power against Minimized Pokemon.

name: Strength
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: String Shot
description: Lowers the target's Speed by 1 stage.

name: Struggle
description: Used automatically when all of the user's other moves have run out of PP or are otherwise inaccessible. The user receives recoil damage equal to 1/4 of its max HP. Struggle is classified as a typeless move and will hit any Pokemon for normal damage.

name: Stun Spore
description: Paralyzes the target.

name: Submission
description: The user receives 1/4 recoil damage.

name: Substitute
description: The user takes one-fourth of its maximum HP to create a substitute; this move fails if the user does not have enough HP for this. Until the substitute is broken it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat modifiers caused by other Pokemon. The user is still affected by Tickle Hail Sandstorm and Attract from behind its Substitute. If a Substitute breaks from a hit during a multistrike move such as Fury Attack the user takes damage from the remaining strikes.

name: Sunny Day
description: Cancels all other weather moves. For 5 turns: freezing is prevented the power of Fire attacks is increased by 50% the power of Water attacks is decreased by 50% Solarbeam fires immediately Thunder becomes 50% accurate and the healing power of Morning Sun Synthesis and Moonlight is increased from 1/2 to 2/3 of the user's max HP. The effects of Sunny Day will last for eight turns if its user is holding Heat Rock.

name: Super Fang
description: This move halves the target's current HP.

name: Superpower
description: Lowers the user's Attack and Defense by 1 stage each after use.

name: Supersonic
description: Confuses the target.

name: Surf
description: Power doubles against a target who is in the middle of using Dive.

name: Swagger
description: Confuses the target and raises its Attack by 2 stages.

name: Swallow
description: This move only works if the user has at least one Stockpile. Restores 1/4 of user's max HP with one Stockpile 1/2 of user's max HP with two Stockpiles and fully restores the user's HP with three Stockpiles.

name: Sweet Kiss
description: Confuses the target.

name: Sweet Scent
description: Lowers the target's Evasion by 1 stage.

name: Swift
description: Ignores Evasion and Accuracy modifiers and never misses except against Protect Detect or a target in the middle of Dig Fly Dive or Bounce.

name: Swords Dance
description: Raises the user's Attack by 2 stages.

name: Synthesis
description: Restores a fraction of the user's max HP depending on the weather: 2/3 during Sunny Day 1/2 during regular weather and 1/4 during Rain Dance Hail and Sandstorm.

name: Tackle
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Tail Glow
description: Raises the user's Special Attack by 2 stages.

name: Tail Whip
description: Lowers the target's Defense by 1 stage.

name: Take Down
description: The user receives 1/4 recoil damage.

name: Taunt
description: Prevents the target from using non-damaging moves for 3 turns. Assist Copycat Me First Metronome Mirror Move and Sleep Talk are prevented during this time but Bide Counter Endeavor Metal Burst and Mirror Coat are not prevented.

name: Teeter Dance
description: Each active Pokemon except the user becomes confused.

name: Teleport
description: Escapes from wild battles; fails automatically in trainer and link battles.

name: Thief
description: Steals the target's held item unless the user is already holding an item or the target has Sticky Hold or Multitype. A stolen item cannot be recovered by using Recycle.

name: Thrash
description: The user attacks uncontrollably for 2-3 turns and then gets confused.

name: Thunder
description: Has a 30% chance to paralyze the target. It also has normal accuracy against mid-air Pokemon who have used Fly or Bounce. During Sunny Day this move has 50% accuracy. During Rain Dance this move will never miss under normal circumstances and has a 30% chance to hit through a target's Protect or Detect.

name: Thunder Wave
description: Paralyzes the target. This move activates Motor Drive.

name: Thunderbolt
description: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.

name: ThunderPunch
description: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.

name: ThunderShock
description: Has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.

name: Tickle
description: Lowers the target's Attack and Defense by 1 stage each.

name: Torment
description: Prevents the target from using the same move for two turns in a row until the target is switched out. The target will use Struggle every other turn if it cannot attack without using the same move.

name: Toxic
description: The target is badly poisoned with the damage caused by poison doubling after each turn. Toxic poisoning will remain with the Pokemon during the battle even after switching out.

name: Transform
description: The user morphs into a near-exact copy of the target. Stats stat modifiers type moves Hidden Power data and appearance are changed; the user's level and HP remain the same and each copied move receives only 5 PP. (If Transform is used by Ditto the effects of Metal Powder and Quick Powder stop working after transformation.)

name: Tri Attack
description: Has a 20% chance to burn paralyze or freeze the target.

name: Trick
description: Exchanges items with the target unless it has Sticky Hold or Multitype. Items lost to this move cannot be recovered by using Recycle.

name: Triple Kick
description: Attacks three times in one turn adding 10 BP for each kick. If a kick misses the move ends instantly; if one of the kicks breaks a target's Substitute the real Pokemon will take damage for the remaining kicks.

name: Twineedle
description: Strikes twice; if the first hit breaks the target's Substitute the real Pokemon will take damage from the second hit. Has a 20% chance to poison the target .

name: Twister
description: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch; power doubles while the target is in mid-air via Fly or Bounce.

name: Uproar
description: The user causes an Uproar and attacks uncontrollably for 3 turns. During the effects of the Uproar active Pokemon cannot fall asleep and sleeping Pokemon sent into battle will wake up.

name: ViceGrip
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Vine Whip
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Vital Throw
description: This move usually goes last. It ignores Evasion and Accuracy modifiers and never misses except against Protect Detect or a target in the middle of Dig Fly Dive or Bounce.

name: Volt Tackle
description: The user receives 1/3 recoil damage; has a 10% chance to paralyze the target.

name: Water Gun
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Water Pulse
description: Has a 20% chance to confuse the target.

name: Water Sport
description: All Fire-type moves are 50% weaker until the user switches out.

name: Water Spout
description: Base power decreases as the user's HP decreases.

name: Waterfall
description: Has a 20% chance to make the target flinch.

name: Weather Ball
description: Base power is 50; Base power doubles and move's type changes during weather effects: becomes Fire-type during Sunny Day Water-type during Rain Dance Ice-type during Hail and Rock-type during Sandstorm.

name: Whirlpool
description: Traps the target for 5-6 turns causing damage equal to 1/16 of its max HP each turn; this trapped effect can be broken by Rapid Spin. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-Turn. Base power also doubles when performed against a Pokemon in the middle of using Dive.

name: Whirlwind
description: Almost always goes last; in trainer battles the target is switched out for a random member of its team. Escapes from wild battles. Has no effect if the target has Suction Cups or used Ingrain.

name: Will-O-Wisp
description: Burns the target. This move activates Flash Fire.

name: Wing Attack
description: Deals damage with no additional effect.

name: Wish
description: At the end of the next turn the active Pokemon from the user's team is healed by 1/2 of the user's HP; this can be any member of the user's team.

name: Withdraw
description: Raises the user's Defense by 1 stage.

name: Wrap
description: Traps the target for 5-6 turns causing damage equal to 1/16 of its max HP each turn; this trapped effect can be broken by Rapid Spin. The target can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass or U-Turn.

name: Yawn
description: If the target stays in battle it falls asleep at the end of the next turn.

name: Zap Cannon
description: Paralyzes the target.
